This paper deals with privacy in IoT networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an optimization framework that incorporates both local differential privacy and information privacy metrics, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of empirical optimization for the nonparametric case, which involves statistical methods (cs.SI) and possibly machine learning as well. Finally, the paper deals with the processing of data from multiple sensors, which could involve distributed systems (cs.DS).
